<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-05-11T19:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="784" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d784">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of the Central
                                    American Court of Justice</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Jose, C. R.</hi></placeName> (<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1910-05-11T19:40:00-05:00" notBefore="1910-05-04T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>).<lb/>(Received May 11, 1910—7.40
                            p.m.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The Central American court of justice acknowledges with sincere thanks
                            your excellency’s cablegram dated yesterday, by which you congratulate
                            it on the mediation it has rendered to secure peace in Nicaragua, and
                            highly appreciates your excellency’s wishes for the establishment of a
                            government of order and prosperity in Nicaragua.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alberto Ucles.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>